WEBVTT

00:25.025 --> 00:27.437
Anyway, what was I saying?

00:28.195 --> 00:29.981
So you did bring me in here to work.

00:30.989 --> 00:32.149
Right, work.

00:32.324 --> 00:36.067
You need to stop blabbering to the world
that I'm writing the Lex Luthor exposé.

00:36.578 --> 00:39.069
It's the biggest story of the year.

00:39.248 --> 00:42.911
|-- I just thought we agreed
that our dating life would be off the record.

00:43.794 --> 00:45.750
We're hiding in a storage closet.

00:45.921 --> 00:47.752
What more do you want from me?

00:48.465 --> 00:52.049
It didn't cross your mind
that inquiring minds might wonder...

00:52.219 --> 00:56.804
...why a rookie basement dweller
is writing this story?

00:57.433 --> 01:00.391
It has nothing to do with us.

01:01.854 --> 01:03.810
Well, if I'm gonna keep our—

01:03.981 --> 01:06.267
This a secret, I need to make sure...

01:06.442 --> 01:10.105
...that the only part of my body
earning me stories is my reporter's nose.

01:11.238 --> 01:13.194
I didn't give you the story.

01:13.365 --> 01:15.572
Lex requested you.

01:16.243 --> 01:17.528
What?

01:18.245 --> 01:19.485
Clark, hi.

01:19.663 --> 01:21.119
It's your daily freak-out call.

01:21.290 --> 01:24.032
Seriously, two weeks with no callback,
what's going on?

01:24.209 --> 01:27.451
Lana said you smoothed everything out
before you went to the Fortress.

01:27.629 --> 01:30.006
I'm tired of lying about you
being in Minnesota.

01:30.174 --> 01:33.382
I'm getting really angry or really scared.

01:33.802 --> 01:35.178
Hey, was that Clark?

01:35.345 --> 01:37.631
He said that he'd ﬁx our satellite
two weeks ago.

01:37.806 --> 01:40.218
It still looks like Jack Frost
puked all over the TV.

01:40.392 --> 01:43.350
Yeah, he's still in Minnesota
spending the holidays with Kara.

01:43.520 --> 01:46.262
Well, when he returns
from those 10,000 frozen lakes...

01:46.440 --> 01:48.647
...I would really like my Daily Show back.

01:49.902 --> 01:53.144
In the meantime, happy holidays.

01:53.322 --> 01:57.031
I had the print shop compile all my research
on LuthorCorp, so there you go.

01:57.201 --> 02:00.318
A hundred and one ways
to make Lex Luthor squirm.

02:00.496 --> 02:03.738
Thanks, coz.
You're actually my ﬁrst legitimate source.

02:04.416 --> 02:07.533
Thank me for convincing you
to break it off with Grant.

02:07.711 --> 02:10.544
Now no one can say you didn't
land this one fair and square.

02:15.427 --> 02:17.418
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

02:26.063 --> 02:28.224
Did anyone lose their phone?

02:31.944 --> 02:32.979
Hello?

02:33.153 --> 02:34.609
You've been ignoring me.

02:35.072 --> 02:37.984
You got the wrong person here.
It's not my phone.

02:38.158 --> 02:40.945
I know, but it's not easy
getting your attention, Lane.

02:41.119 --> 02:44.077
You erased my e-mails.
You tossed my letters.

02:44.706 --> 02:46.867
I'm trying to help you bring down
Lex Luthor.

02:47.960 --> 02:51.544
Ah, hey, I appreciate that, but when
it comes to LuthorCorp conspiracies...

02:51.713 --> 02:53.840
...a lot gets tossed in the crazy bin.

02:54.007 --> 02:56.339
See if this gets me
to the top of the pile, Lane.

02:56.510 --> 02:57.920
There's a bomb on your cousin.

03:03.100 --> 03:04.431
If you try to get help...

03:04.601 --> 03:08.264
...if you so much as whisper
a single word to anyone...

03:08.438 --> 03:09.769
...Chloe dies.

03:11.859 --> 03:13.724
Do l have your attention now?

04:12.044 --> 04:14.035
[BOTH GRUNTING]

04:30.854 --> 04:34.972
When I suggested a dinner meeting, I was
hoping to consume calories, not burn them.

04:35.150 --> 04:38.688
Technically, I should be stringing popcorn
at a Suicide Slums nursing home...

04:38.862 --> 04:41.899
...but then I wouldn't have the pleasure
of beating you.

04:42.074 --> 04:46.534
In that case, I'm afraid you've traded
one business event for another.

04:47.371 --> 04:50.283
I want you to ask someone else
to write your exposé.

04:50.457 --> 04:54.826
Lois has a mysterious way of diving for
a penny and coming up with the Holy Grail.

04:55.253 --> 04:58.666
I appreciate your brotherly concern
but I don't have anything to hide.

04:58.840 --> 05:00.967
Well, that's certainly
a cavalier approach...

05:01.134 --> 05:04.877
...to a murder accusation
and a public divorce.

05:05.847 --> 05:07.553
Lois knows what she wants, Lex.

05:08.058 --> 05:09.218
She'll get to you.

05:09.393 --> 05:11.975
Or more importantly, get to you.

05:12.145 --> 05:14.727
For someone who claims
to have broken it off with her...

05:14.898 --> 05:17.355
...you certainly sound concerned
by what she uncovers.

05:17.526 --> 05:20.233
I'm not the one Lois has
a vendetta against.

05:21.613 --> 05:24.104
I thought you would have learned
by now.

05:25.659 --> 05:28.321
| always ﬁnd a way to win in the end.

05:34.751 --> 05:36.366
LOIS:
Slow down, Adrian.

05:36.545 --> 05:38.581
I'm not exactly Mozart on the keyboard.

05:38.755 --> 05:42.839
I got everything up to you being
an escaped clone from the LuthorCorp.

05:43.010 --> 05:45.046
ADRIAN:
lMth a body aging on overdrive.

05:45.220 --> 05:47.381
I'll be dead any day now.

05:48.557 --> 05:51.390
You'd think Lex Luthor would have
kinks like that worked out.

05:51.560 --> 05:54.802
I know, it sounds crazy,
but you need to believe me.

05:55.355 --> 05:58.438
It doesn't matter what I believe.
I am printing this to protect my cousin.

05:58.608 --> 06:00.394
Take it from a fellow Lex hater...

06:00.569 --> 06:02.901
...the Planet won't print anything
without proof.

06:03.071 --> 06:04.447
Just write the story.

06:04.614 --> 06:08.482
In a couple of hours, every newspaper
in the country will be begging for it.

06:12.998 --> 06:14.954
Come on.

06:17.377 --> 06:18.878
What?

06:23.133 --> 06:24.964
[PHONE RINGING]

06:29.306 --> 06:31.137
ADRIAN:
You don't think I covered my bases?

06:31.308 --> 06:32.969
Don't try anything cute.

06:33.143 --> 06:35.725
Yeah, I wanna send a photographer....

06:37.564 --> 06:39.145
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

07:09.054 --> 07:10.544
[MAN GRUNTS]

07:10.722 --> 07:12.508
Are you nuts? What are you doing?

07:12.933 --> 07:14.673
I saw you staring at me.

07:14.851 --> 07:16.352
Yeah? So? You're a babe.

07:16.520 --> 07:18.727
Great. You're a terrorist and a pervert.

07:18.897 --> 07:20.307
Deactivate the bomb.

07:20.482 --> 07:22.518
Whoa, whoa. Bomb? What bomb?

07:23.193 --> 07:24.683
Very funny.

07:27.322 --> 07:28.482
[DIALING]

07:28.657 --> 07:29.692
[LINE RINGS]

07:29.866 --> 07:32.608
WOMAN:
Ofﬁce America, how may I help you?

07:33.787 --> 07:34.822
Oh, crap.

07:35.956 --> 07:37.196
What the hell's going on?

07:37.374 --> 07:38.910
Uh....

07:39.209 --> 07:41.541
I am so sorry.
I thought you were someone else.

07:42.879 --> 07:44.995
You need some serious help, lady.

07:45.173 --> 07:46.879
I'm getting security.

07:48.009 --> 07:49.465
Great.

07:50.428 --> 07:52.840
Pull yourself together, Lois.

07:53.849 --> 07:55.885
Hey, man. I told you I was sorry.

07:58.895 --> 08:00.226
[MAN GASPS]

08:01.565 --> 08:02.896
[LOIS GRUNTS]

08:05.193 --> 08:07.184
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

08:15.745 --> 08:18.122
ADRIAN:
I told you to shut your mouth.

08:18.290 --> 08:21.532
Now, you're gonna walk out
and ﬁnish the story like nothing happened.

08:21.710 --> 08:23.792
l'll clean up your mess.

08:24.129 --> 08:25.994
You killed him.

08:26.173 --> 08:28.585
And next time, it'll be Chloe.

08:41.855 --> 08:43.391
CLARK:
Lana.

08:45.650 --> 08:47.436
Clark.

08:47.777 --> 08:49.392
Oh, my God.

08:49.571 --> 08:51.653
You had me so worried.

08:53.575 --> 08:55.941
Were you in your Fortress
this entire time?

08:56.119 --> 08:59.486
Time is so different there.
I didn't realize how long I was gone for.

08:59.664 --> 09:00.949
Did you ﬁnd Kara?

09:02.042 --> 09:04.249
There was nothing I could do.

09:04.920 --> 09:08.333
I think it's time I accept the fact
that she's gone and move on.

09:10.008 --> 09:12.465
Kind of a tall order these days.

09:13.762 --> 09:15.627
Well, I'm back and you're here.

09:15.805 --> 09:17.306
That's what matters now.

09:18.642 --> 09:23.136
Clark, as much as I have missed you, l--

09:23.355 --> 09:26.142
I think maybe being apart
was good for us.

09:28.068 --> 09:32.562
I had some time to think,
to evaluate my priorities.

09:34.991 --> 09:39.155
I'm dropping my ﬁxation on Lex
and all of his projects.

09:40.413 --> 09:43.405
I had some time
to do some thinking myself.

09:44.334 --> 09:47.417
I may know a way for us to get back
on the same page.

09:50.173 --> 09:52.710
I need you to show me everything
you have on Lex.

09:53.426 --> 09:55.542
We'll get him together.

10:01.184 --> 10:03.846
This isn't exactly hot chocolate
on the boardwalk.

10:04.020 --> 10:05.931
What are we doing here?

10:06.564 --> 10:08.555
What I drove you to do.

10:09.484 --> 10:11.645
If this is some attempt at a guilt trip...

10:12.570 --> 10:15.357
...I haven't been watching Lex for weeks.

10:16.366 --> 10:19.108
Lana, it's time I face what I did to you.

10:19.286 --> 10:20.867
What you did?

10:21.329 --> 10:23.240
CLARK:
What I didn't do.

10:23.873 --> 10:26.910
Let you open up
about how much Lex hurt you.

10:27.961 --> 10:31.704
I wanted you to just move on,
forget it ever happened, but you couldn't.

10:33.633 --> 10:36.045
So you hid your feelings
and you hid your research.

10:36.219 --> 10:40.212
You must have known I felt responsible for
everything Lex did while you were with him.

10:40.682 --> 10:43.765
Everything he did to you
while you were protecting me.

10:43.935 --> 10:46.221
Lex is the villain here, not you.

10:46.688 --> 10:48.895
I know, that's what I'm saying.

10:50.650 --> 10:52.390
Lex needs to be put behind bars, Lana.

10:52.569 --> 10:54.184
You were right.

10:56.239 --> 10:58.230
I think you hold the key.

11:10.253 --> 11:11.868
Scion.

11:13.798 --> 11:15.914
Or what's left of it.

11:24.267 --> 11:28.556
That vial, I must have destroyed it
when l wrecked Lex's lab.

11:28.730 --> 11:32.769
Before you showed up, he was talking
about some alien invasion.

11:34.069 --> 11:36.401
Do you think that this has something
to do with it?

11:37.280 --> 11:40.238
Lana, if this is alien technology,
you didn't destroy it.

11:45.497 --> 11:46.703
Lana, what is it?

11:46.873 --> 11:50.081
If you really want to partner with me
on this...

11:50.251 --> 11:54.665
...then I think it's time you see everything
that I found on Project Scion.

12:14.192 --> 12:15.477
Any outgoing?

12:16.486 --> 12:18.477
Yeah, right here.

12:39.342 --> 12:41.173
Come on, lady.

12:45.432 --> 12:47.423
CHLOE:
Oh, thanks.

12:52.355 --> 12:55.643
Hey, so good news.
Clark is back from the Twin Cities...

12:55.817 --> 12:59.184
...so I'm just gonna drop off my rewrite
and head over and say hello.

12:59.362 --> 13:00.693
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

13:06.035 --> 13:07.866
Great, cool.

13:09.747 --> 13:13.365
So I'll, uh, send him your warmest?

13:15.211 --> 13:18.248
I'm sorry, I'm just busy prepping
the interview.

13:18.756 --> 13:21.543
-You sure everything's all right?
-Yeah, just peachy.

13:21.718 --> 13:23.174
See you later.

13:32.270 --> 13:35.387
If we're taking Lex head-on,
there's no point in sugarcoating it.

13:35.565 --> 13:37.806
I think Scion might be more alive
than we thought.

13:37.984 --> 13:39.394
Lex doesn't know you found it?

13:39.569 --> 13:42.481
Not so much an "it" as a "her."

13:45.158 --> 13:49.572
While you were gone, Casey Brock,
a LuthorCorp lab tech working on Scion...

13:49.746 --> 13:52.237
...was found half-conscious in an alley.

13:52.707 --> 13:55.744
She was exhibiting
random incoherent speech patterns...

13:55.919 --> 13:59.082
...and was suffering
from toxic levels of metal poisoning.

13:59.255 --> 14:00.756
So you had her quarantined.

14:00.924 --> 14:02.255
What other choice did I have?

14:02.425 --> 14:04.165
When I heard about Casey's symptoms...

14:04.344 --> 14:08.462
...I had my contacts at the Isis Foundation
have her transferred down here.

14:11.809 --> 14:13.140
It is extreme.

14:13.311 --> 14:15.302
But if she had something to do
with Scion...

14:15.480 --> 14:19.098
...I couldn't have other patients exposed
to whatever was in her bloodstream.

14:19.275 --> 14:21.106
What do you mean "was"?

14:22.111 --> 14:26.445
Overnight, the metal content in her body
dropped dramatically.

14:26.616 --> 14:31.076
My team could ﬁnd hardly any trace
of zinc, magnesium or iron.

14:32.163 --> 14:36.281
So whatever it was siphoned
her body's natural minerals and moved on.

14:36.918 --> 14:38.909
[WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

14:41.673 --> 14:43.755
She's been doing that
since she was admitted.

14:45.051 --> 14:47.542
No one understands what she's saying.

14:52.976 --> 14:54.136
I'm not surprised.

14:57.021 --> 14:59.273
She's speaking Kryptonian.

15:14.622 --> 15:17.159
-Jimmy.
-Oh, uh....

15:17.333 --> 15:19.665
You know what,
I'll just grab the next one.

15:19.836 --> 15:22.498
Don't be ridiculous,
there's plenty of room.

15:23.131 --> 15:26.840
Yeah, you know, the thing is
is that I'm going the other way.

15:27.719 --> 15:28.799
We're in the basement.

15:28.970 --> 15:31.632
Travel options are kind of limited.

15:31.973 --> 15:34.680
Oh. Right.

15:46.154 --> 15:48.145
[CHRISTMAS ELEVATOR
MUSIC PLAYING]

15:55.330 --> 15:57.742
-You going to the Christmas party later?
-No.

15:57.915 --> 16:01.043
I think I'm gonna pull my Scrooge card
on this one and stay home.

16:01.210 --> 16:04.668
I heard Susan from HR
is bringing mistletoe tonight.

16:05.131 --> 16:08.043
I know. I'm all about
the amusement factor.

16:09.052 --> 16:11.714
If I remember correctly,
there was mistletoe last year.

16:11.888 --> 16:13.799
Didn't seem to stop you.

16:14.599 --> 16:18.467
Yeah, well, that was different.
I mean, I already had my sights set on...

16:20.647 --> 16:22.103
...you.

16:29.906 --> 16:31.567
Oh, my God.

16:36.913 --> 16:38.744
[ELEVATOR SCREECHES]

16:43.169 --> 16:44.830
[PUSHING BUTTONS]

16:47.590 --> 16:49.171
We're stuck.

16:51.219 --> 16:52.925
With a bomb.

17:12.740 --> 17:13.980
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

17:14.158 --> 17:16.149
MAN:
Any civil servant...

17:19.247 --> 17:21.784
ADRIAN:
Gotta say, much cuter in person.

17:22.750 --> 17:24.331
Adrian.

17:24.877 --> 17:26.538
Draw attention to yourself...

17:26.713 --> 17:29.796
...and I'll decorate that elevator
with your cousin.

17:32.051 --> 17:33.632
Where's my story?

17:41.686 --> 17:43.472
Now, I haven't read 0-4 for Dummies...

17:43.646 --> 17:48.015
...but I'm guessing that if we're babysitting
a bomb, it'll be somewhere in this pile.

17:50.653 --> 17:54.145
-This is, uh--
-Not supposed to be in there.

18:02.331 --> 18:05.789
Jimmy, I seriously doubt
my Secret Santa planted a--

18:10.173 --> 18:11.629
Oh, wow.

18:11.799 --> 18:14.381
I have the worst Secret Santa ever.

18:20.850 --> 18:22.681
LOIS:
It's all in there.

18:23.352 --> 18:26.515
"LuthorCorp's First Functioning Clone."

18:28.316 --> 18:31.479
Something tells me you wouldn't go this far
if it weren't the truth.

18:38.367 --> 18:41.154
My body won't hold out much longer.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.615
I'll be dead by Christmas.

18:47.001 --> 18:49.117
You celebrate Christmas, Lane?

18:49.670 --> 18:51.080
Yeah.

18:52.715 --> 18:55.957
We used to send out
the Christmas portrait every year.

18:57.386 --> 18:59.092
Me in an ugly sweater.

18:59.263 --> 19:01.845
My mom with her take smile.

19:02.016 --> 19:03.347
My dad...

19:04.310 --> 19:06.551
...missing his football game.

19:08.564 --> 19:12.523
Then you must know how it feels
when one of them is in danger.

19:15.363 --> 19:16.819
Hm.

19:19.575 --> 19:21.281
You'd think.

19:25.164 --> 19:27.780
After I escaped from LuthorCorp,
I went looking for them.

19:27.959 --> 19:30.416
My parents, my Christmas memories.

19:31.838 --> 19:35.376
It's all a ﬁction some scientist
downloaded into my brain.

19:36.968 --> 19:39.584
Yet I remember them like they're real.

19:42.265 --> 19:46.599
And come tomorrow morning's early edition,
the world will know what Lex did to you.

19:46.769 --> 19:49.226
Now, please, let my cousin go.

19:49.397 --> 19:52.264
The deal was I write the story,
you give me Chloe.

19:52.441 --> 19:54.272
Not quite.

19:54.777 --> 19:57.564
You need to force Lex
to confess what he's done.

20:00.199 --> 20:03.157
Don't make me remind you
what's at stake.

20:14.505 --> 20:16.882
If you can hear me,
we're in the center elevator...

20:17.049 --> 20:19.756
...at the Daily Planet with a bomb.

20:19.927 --> 20:22.964
-Hurry please, Clark.
-Clark?

20:23.139 --> 20:24.925
-Whoa! Ah!
-Ow!

20:25.099 --> 20:26.214
CHLOE:
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

20:26.392 --> 20:28.758
You waste your one phone call on Clark?

20:28.936 --> 20:30.767
I didn't realize we had so few ﬂares.

20:30.938 --> 20:33.145
Regardless, you call Clark
before you dial 911?

20:33.316 --> 20:35.853
What's he gonna do?
Dismantle the bomb with his hair?

20:37.194 --> 20:40.186
Lois snuck me a note
which means that she's under surveillance...

20:40.364 --> 20:41.979
...by whoever's orchestrating this.

20:42.158 --> 20:45.446
Now, how would it look if a SWAT parade
trampled through the bullpen?

20:54.503 --> 20:56.459
ADRIAN:
Smile at the nice people.

21:00.259 --> 21:02.671
See, no one suspects a thing.

21:05.097 --> 21:06.177
You have your bag?

21:07.892 --> 21:09.348
[CLEARS THROAT]

21:09.977 --> 21:12.059
My ﬁnger is on the detonator.

21:12.313 --> 21:16.226
No confession, your cousin dies.
Try to warn them, your cousin dies.

21:17.902 --> 21:19.893
Let's go see the boss.

21:21.739 --> 21:24.606
CLARK: Everything Casey has been rambling
turns out to be a hex code.

21:24.784 --> 21:27.821
-A pattern of Kryptonian zeroes and ones.
-Right.

21:27.995 --> 21:32.034
Chloe once used a program to ﬁnd a pattern
in Kryptonian symbols Lionel was scribbling.

21:32.500 --> 21:34.832
Maybe she can translate this one.

21:35.544 --> 21:37.751
Not if she's not here.

21:44.845 --> 21:46.221
Here she is.

21:46.389 --> 21:48.220
Right on time.

21:50.184 --> 21:52.675
Mr. Luthor, you know Lois Lane.

21:52.853 --> 21:55.344
Well, it certainly has been a while,
hasn't it?

21:55.523 --> 21:59.311
I haven't seen Ms. Lane since I caught her
breaking into my ofﬁce.

22:01.612 --> 22:02.727
Yeah, long time.

22:03.906 --> 22:06.693
-Shall we?
-Please.

22:07.576 --> 22:09.953
Big story. Ahem. Exciting.

22:10.121 --> 22:12.032
Maybe you should
just ask your questions.

22:13.249 --> 22:15.035
Right, questions.

22:15.209 --> 22:17.074
Ask him about Project Gemini.

22:18.254 --> 22:22.418
Mr. Luthor, perhaps we could start
by discussing Project Gemini.

22:24.593 --> 22:25.924
Excuse me?

22:26.095 --> 22:28.552
My sources tell me you run
some kind of an ant farm...

22:28.723 --> 22:30.588
...except instead of ants, it's humans...

22:30.766 --> 22:33.382
-...and instead of a farm, it's a lab.
-Lois.

22:33.561 --> 22:37.179
Not that you're renowned
for your eloquence, Lois...

22:37.356 --> 22:39.893
...but I have no idea
what you're talking about.

22:40.484 --> 22:41.769
Human cloning.

22:41.944 --> 22:44.276
The replication of a DNA sequence...

22:44.447 --> 22:47.530
...produced from
a single identical ancestor.

22:48.784 --> 22:50.285
My mistake.

22:50.453 --> 22:53.286
I didn't realize you'd be pitching me
a Hollywood movie.

22:53.456 --> 22:56.368
Is this how you run your paper,
Mr. Gabriel?

22:57.168 --> 22:58.829
Tell him who he's talking to.

22:59.628 --> 23:00.959
Adrian sends his best.

23:04.800 --> 23:06.961
Should that name mean something?

23:07.136 --> 23:08.467
Now, reach in your briefcase.

23:13.309 --> 23:15.049
Oh, my God.

23:19.774 --> 23:22.436
Aim it at Grant and get the truth.

23:22.735 --> 23:24.817
It's time for the truth, Lex.

23:28.240 --> 23:29.980
Lie again...

23:33.329 --> 23:35.115
...Grant Gabriel dies.

23:35.289 --> 23:36.995
Lois, put down the gun.

23:37.166 --> 23:38.656
Just answer the question.

23:38.834 --> 23:41.667
-Lane, what the hell are you doing?
-Getting the truth.

23:41.837 --> 23:43.338
Lex, there's no time.

23:43.506 --> 23:46.714
Why does Adrian have a memory
for a life that doesn't exist?

23:47.176 --> 23:49.007
I don't know who Adrian is.

23:49.178 --> 23:50.338
Well, I wrote a story.

23:50.846 --> 23:52.347
He grew up outside Philly.

23:52.515 --> 23:54.506
Played point guard for Homestead High.

23:54.683 --> 23:57.470
Got his ﬁrst job on the obituary beat
at the Liberty Times.

23:57.645 --> 24:00.512
That is where he ﬁrst got noticed
as the editor in Alaska.

24:00.689 --> 24:02.020
First in sports, then--

24:02.191 --> 24:03.180
[LOIS GRUNTS]

24:05.861 --> 24:07.067
What are you doing?

24:08.322 --> 24:10.859
Someone was pulling her strings.

24:12.243 --> 24:13.733
I took her out of the equation.

24:13.911 --> 24:15.492
So she wouldn't hear the truth?

24:15.663 --> 24:17.528
Those were my memories, Lex.

24:17.706 --> 24:19.617
You're the editor of a major newspaper.

24:19.792 --> 24:21.328
That information is everywhere.

24:21.627 --> 24:24.414
ADRIAN: What about the time my mom
got me a red-and-green dirt bike...

24:24.588 --> 24:25.839
...for my seventh birthday?

24:27.007 --> 24:29.214
I rode that thing everywhere.

24:29.552 --> 24:32.635
-Thought I could pedal--
-Until the chain wore out.

24:33.389 --> 24:35.129
That's the one.

24:37.268 --> 24:40.431
I saw your picture in the paper
and realized we had a lot in common.

24:40.604 --> 24:43.266
-Who the hell are you?
-Lex, let him talk.

24:44.733 --> 24:46.564
How do you have my memories?

24:46.986 --> 24:48.851
Because Lex made me.

24:51.031 --> 24:52.942
And when I didn't work...

24:54.076 --> 24:55.816
...he made you.

24:56.745 --> 24:58.076
What's he talking about, Lex?

24:59.123 --> 25:01.580
Congratulations, Grant.
You're the perfect clone.

25:02.001 --> 25:03.457
He's insane.

25:06.547 --> 25:08.162
You're me?

25:09.091 --> 25:10.797
Same DNA.

25:10.968 --> 25:12.208
Same back-story.

25:12.386 --> 25:15.423
The only difference is that you worked
and I didn't.

25:19.435 --> 25:22.142
Lionel giving me up for adoption.

25:22.354 --> 25:24.015
-My Harvard degree.
-Harvard degree.

25:24.190 --> 25:25.930
-The paper.
-The paper.

25:28.944 --> 25:30.650
It's all lies.

25:33.032 --> 25:34.772
Am I even your brother?

25:34.950 --> 25:35.939
Brother?

25:36.118 --> 25:38.450
GRANT:
Who died when Lex was 12.

25:38.913 --> 25:40.369
You created me in a test tube...

25:40.539 --> 25:42.996
...kept me like some pet,
so you could have a brother?

25:43.167 --> 25:46.375
-ls that why you couldn't get rid of me?
-You're not my brother!

25:49.590 --> 25:50.750
You're a mistake.

25:51.300 --> 25:52.540
[GASPS]

25:57.890 --> 25:59.881
[BEEPING]

26:04.104 --> 26:05.605
[BEEPING]

26:06.273 --> 26:07.979
CHLOE:
Oh, my God.

26:08.359 --> 26:11.943
-Help! Help!
-Help! Help us! Help!

26:20.329 --> 26:23.162
JIMMY: Help us! Help!
CHLOE: Help! Help!

26:23.666 --> 26:26.749
It's no use. If someone could've heard us,
they would've by now.

26:28.212 --> 26:30.328
Jimmy, I don't think
we're gonna make it.

26:30.506 --> 26:32.838
[CHRISTMAS ELEVATOR
MUSIC PLAYING]

26:38.264 --> 26:40.676
I'm not gonna cart my baggage
through the afterlife.

26:40.849 --> 26:42.805
There's something I have to share
with you.

26:42.977 --> 26:46.185
Though I always imagined this
playing out to a Kelly Clarkson song...

26:46.355 --> 26:47.845
...not some "Jingle Bells" Muzak.

26:48.023 --> 26:50.560
-Chloe, time is sort of the essence here.
-Right, okay.

26:50.734 --> 26:52.690
I didn't pull away from our relationship...

26:52.861 --> 26:54.817
...because there was
anything wrong with us.

26:54.989 --> 26:58.197
I mean, we were—
Well, at least, you were perfect.

26:58.367 --> 27:00.858
It was just me. I'm— I'm different.

27:04.540 --> 27:06.371
I'm a meteor freak.

27:10.879 --> 27:13.370
Some feedback would be awesome
right now.

27:14.174 --> 27:15.675
Okay.

27:16.719 --> 27:19.005
If we're going out with no regrets.

27:28.897 --> 27:30.979
Straight to her voice mail.

27:39.867 --> 27:42.449
Oh, my God. Clark, look at this.

27:49.793 --> 27:52.330
[VOICES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

27:54.340 --> 27:56.331
[BOMB BEEPING]

28:42.471 --> 28:43.711
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

29:05.452 --> 29:07.443
[LOIS GROANING]

29:11.458 --> 29:13.449
Move it, Holyﬁeld.

29:14.753 --> 29:16.334
I need to ﬁnd Chloe.

29:16.505 --> 29:18.917
Security just pulled her from the elevator.

29:19.091 --> 29:22.675
Unfortunately, your puppeteer, Adrian,
managed to escape.

29:22.845 --> 29:24.051
What about Grant?

29:24.513 --> 29:28.722
He went to ﬁnd you a medic,
but I see you bounced backjust ﬁne.

29:29.935 --> 29:32.893
Wish I could say the same thing
about your career.

29:33.063 --> 29:35.054
After the little ditty Adrian inspired...

29:35.232 --> 29:38.770
...l'm exposing your morbid science fair
to the world.

29:39.403 --> 29:40.939
LEX:
Really?

29:42.364 --> 29:44.195
With what evidence?

29:44.741 --> 29:47.198
The word of some Belle Reve runaway?

29:47.369 --> 29:51.533
Look, not that it matters,
but you're no longer writing my exposé.

29:52.624 --> 29:54.125
Uh-uh.

29:54.543 --> 29:57.034
You'll have to take that up with my boss.

29:58.380 --> 30:00.371
I am your boss.

30:01.216 --> 30:03.548
Merry Christmas, Lois.

30:03.719 --> 30:06.381
I just bought the Daily Planet.

30:16.231 --> 30:20.474
If you wanna split early,
I think today qualiﬁes as on-the-job stress.

30:20.652 --> 30:22.483
I was just ﬁnishing up.

30:22.654 --> 30:25.441
But I'm glad you're here, actually.

30:25.991 --> 30:27.902
About the kiss in the elevator.

30:28.076 --> 30:32.194
I do this thing
when I think the world is ending.

30:32.372 --> 30:35.239
And I grab the ﬁrst guy I see...

30:35.417 --> 30:37.908
...and sort of end up in a lip lock.

30:38.086 --> 30:39.542
Oh.

30:40.005 --> 30:42.087
Yeah, me too.

30:42.591 --> 30:45.458
I mean, girl, not guy. Obviously.

30:47.387 --> 30:49.844
And obviously, there's Kara.

30:52.142 --> 30:53.598
Yeah.

30:54.686 --> 30:56.893
But this wasn't about her.

31:01.652 --> 31:05.395
Chloe, more than goodbye was said
in that elevator.

31:06.406 --> 31:09.239
I just-- I wish it didn't take
a near-death experience...

31:09.409 --> 31:12.025
...for you to feel comfortable
telling me the truth.

31:12.454 --> 31:14.945
I know. Trust me, Jimmy.

31:15.123 --> 31:18.991
I've been struggling to tell you
about my meteor infection for so long.

31:20.837 --> 31:23.374
What did I do to make you think that
I wouldn't accept you?

31:23.549 --> 31:27.337
Nothing. I mean,
I guess I always knew that you would, it—

31:28.387 --> 31:31.971
The real battle was accepting myself.

31:34.142 --> 31:36.474
I hope this means that you have.

31:42.693 --> 31:44.183
So...

31:44.695 --> 31:47.186
...can I assume that
that special ability has to do...

31:47.364 --> 31:50.527
...with that super-sized brain
inside your head?

31:50.701 --> 31:54.444
No. My nerd is all natural.

31:58.333 --> 32:00.244
Oh, my God.

32:02.879 --> 32:04.835
Can you ﬂy?

32:15.559 --> 32:17.345
Here, Jimmy.

32:20.647 --> 32:22.387
Just watch.

32:55.682 --> 32:59.721
I didn't really think--

33:02.022 --> 33:04.308
Where were you in ninth-grade rugby?

33:04.733 --> 33:08.351
Believe me, no golden trophy
is worth these side effects.

33:08.528 --> 33:10.905
-You okay?
-Yeah, I'm ﬁne.

33:11.323 --> 33:13.063
Can you just promise me...

33:13.241 --> 33:16.574
...that we'll keep this between me,
you and my Neosporin?

33:19.373 --> 33:21.079
I promise.

33:24.252 --> 33:26.243
You're still the same Chloe.

33:33.679 --> 33:35.089
[SIGHS]

33:50.779 --> 33:52.519
The last of the acquisition documents.

33:52.698 --> 33:54.529
Come midnight, the paper's yours.

33:54.700 --> 33:57.487
Give me the names and bios
of everyone on staff.

33:57.661 --> 33:59.322
It's time to get rid of our deadwood.

33:59.496 --> 34:00.531
[DOOR OPENS]

34:00.706 --> 34:02.788
Congratulations on the Daily Planet.

34:03.625 --> 34:05.286
Wonderful.

34:05.711 --> 34:09.454
One more piece of my life you can control,
starting with my creation.

34:09.923 --> 34:13.882
I can't believe you let that lunatic
sneak his ideas into your head.

34:14.177 --> 34:16.042
You're my brother.

34:16.888 --> 34:18.298
No, Lex.

34:18.473 --> 34:20.213
I'm an experiment.

34:20.392 --> 34:24.510
Beneath all that arrogance,
your cracks are starting to show.

34:24.980 --> 34:27.938
Did you really think
you could keep this a secret?

34:28.108 --> 34:31.396
Or are you so desperate
to mean something to someone...

34:31.570 --> 34:33.231
...it was worth the risk?

34:34.072 --> 34:36.654
You can't punish me
for wanting a family.

34:37.409 --> 34:39.024
How am I supposed to feel?

34:39.202 --> 34:42.911
Being the product of a man who's
destroyed everything he's ever touched.

34:43.081 --> 34:44.491
No.

34:45.250 --> 34:47.332
You're different, Julian.

34:48.086 --> 34:50.327
If I didn't love you,
you wouldn't be here.

34:50.839 --> 34:54.172
I'm living proof
you've forgotten how to love.

34:54.968 --> 34:56.504
But if you wanna play God...

34:56.678 --> 34:59.590
...you might wanna remember
his greatest gift.

35:00.015 --> 35:01.801
Free will.

35:02.851 --> 35:05.888
Let me live my life.

35:25.415 --> 35:26.746
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

35:36.301 --> 35:38.292
Oh, great. I'm ﬁred, aren't I?

35:39.888 --> 35:44.222
Well, luckily, ljust ﬁnished putting
the bells and whistles on my résumé.

35:44.392 --> 35:46.132
I would hire me in a second.

35:46.311 --> 35:48.222
Lois, you're not ﬁred.

35:48.396 --> 35:53.356
Lex actually asks that you speciﬁcally
remain on the team.

35:53.527 --> 35:56.143
Me? Great.

35:56.321 --> 35:59.734
Can't wait to watch him dull
his shredder with my stories.

36:00.367 --> 36:02.824
You wanna bury the truth,
buy the media.

36:04.621 --> 36:07.658
But the fact that you showed up
on my doorstep...

36:07.833 --> 36:10.575
...means somebody's ready
to spread good news.

36:10.752 --> 36:14.210
Does this house call
mean we're coming out?

36:18.093 --> 36:20.630
Actually, it means we're breaking up.

36:26.268 --> 36:27.599
Oh.

36:31.273 --> 36:35.812
Today was just an example
of why it's not a good idea...

36:35.986 --> 36:38.318
...for us to be together
and work together.

36:38.488 --> 36:40.649
It's too complicated.

36:41.825 --> 36:45.989
And I didn't even drag you to all the places
I usually ruin a relationship.

36:49.916 --> 36:53.875
Well, when you do decide
to take that trip...

36:55.005 --> 36:56.870
...he's a lucky guy.

37:00.468 --> 37:03.596
Whoever he is, we sure as hell
aren't gonna work together.

37:09.352 --> 37:11.468
So how are we gonna liquidate?

37:11.646 --> 37:14.228
You'll take the elevator
and I'll take the stairs?

37:17.319 --> 37:19.651
Don't be ridiculous, Lane.

37:20.238 --> 37:22.194
I'll take the stairs.

37:40.550 --> 37:43.337
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

37:52.437 --> 37:55.975
I had to rev my geek into ﬁfth
in order to crack that hex code.

37:56.149 --> 37:57.889
Just think of it as a thank-you...

37:58.068 --> 38:00.775
...for channeling your
inner Bruce Willis yesterday.

38:00.946 --> 38:03.858
I'm sorry it took till the last second
for me to get there.

38:04.032 --> 38:06.193
I don't know where I'd be without you.

38:07.035 --> 38:08.525
Thanks.

38:09.120 --> 38:10.701
Did I mention that I missed you?

38:12.874 --> 38:14.375
So this pattern, it made sense?

38:14.834 --> 38:18.372
Well, to me, not so much.
But to a computer, it's scripture.

38:18.546 --> 38:20.377
The numbers represent an
error message...

38:20.548 --> 38:23.540
...that high-tech systems encounter
when they can't boot up.

38:24.386 --> 38:27.549
And it's repeating because
a computer keeps trying to start.

38:27.722 --> 38:28.882
Exactly.

38:29.057 --> 38:31.548
I think the sequence is learning
from its mistakes...

38:31.726 --> 38:34.968
...and getting closer
to successfully loading.

38:35.814 --> 38:38.351
That's not my favorite look.

38:39.109 --> 38:42.192
Chloe, this started as metallic ﬂuid
inside a vial.

38:42.362 --> 38:45.854
It's now evolved
into technology that's willing to kill.

38:48.910 --> 38:51.071
It's the Brain lnterActive Construct.

38:51.913 --> 38:54.905
Clark, you think that this is Milton Fine?

38:55.709 --> 38:58.075
But you turned off General Zod's PDA...

38:58.253 --> 39:00.869
...after he spread that computer virus
across the world.

39:01.047 --> 39:03.333
If any part of him was left behind
to regenerate...

39:03.508 --> 39:05.009
...then Fine can be out there.

39:05.176 --> 39:06.507
[DOOR OPENS]

39:09.681 --> 39:11.421
Chloe, hey.

39:13.351 --> 39:16.184
-I didn't know that you were--
-Just leaving.

39:17.147 --> 39:20.560
Do you wanna stay?
I kind of overloaded on Danishes.

39:20.734 --> 39:22.099
No, thanks.

39:22.277 --> 39:24.359
Lois is actually
taking me out for breakfast.

39:24.529 --> 39:27.271
She's deemed it National Chloe Sullivan Day
or something.

39:27.741 --> 39:29.572
I'll call you.

39:30.744 --> 39:33.952
-What's the occasion?
-Your safe return from the Fortress.

39:34.122 --> 39:36.283
Christmas came early this year.

39:36.708 --> 39:38.790
I've missed that smile.

39:39.127 --> 39:40.788
Me too.

39:41.671 --> 39:45.163
To be honest, Clark,
after everything I shared yesterday...

39:45.341 --> 39:49.129
...l was worried that I'd scare you away.

39:49.846 --> 39:52.053
But I've never felt closer.

39:54.517 --> 39:56.974
I realized something when I was gone.

39:57.771 --> 40:01.309
That feelings, good or bad,
they don't just disappear.

40:01.566 --> 40:03.306
No matter who you are.

40:05.695 --> 40:07.981
Are we still talking about Lex?

40:10.075 --> 40:12.066
I'm talking about us.

40:15.413 --> 40:16.698
Yesterday, when I saw you...

40:16.873 --> 40:19.615
...it was like I fell in love with you
all over again.

41:31.239 --> 41:33.230
[ENGLISH SDH]
